         <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#CMR">
            <p>The burial niche <foreign>eisostē</foreign> belongs to Marcus Aurelius Zenon, son of Turbo, son of Trophimus; in it has been buried Marcus Aurelius Eutychos, the one who reared him, 
               and <supplied reason="subaudible">shall be buried</supplied> whomever Zenon may wish.
               If anyone should exhume Eutychos, or bury another <supplied reason="subaudible">person</supplied> without the consent of Zenon, the person who does such a thing shall 
               pay to the most sacred treasury <supplied reason="explanation">the Roman imperial fiscus</supplied> one thousand silver denarii, of which one-third shall belong 
               to the person who prosecutes [the case].
               A copy of the inscription was deposited in the property-archive of the Aphrodisians during the fifth stephanephorate of Titus Flavius Chaireas, in the month of Xandikos.</p>
         </div>
